<subsection xml:id="subsec-squares-of-numbers-from-a-calculator">
    <title>Squares of numbers from a calculator</title>
    <p>
    A calculator is a portable device used to perform different mathematical calculations, such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.    
    </p>
    <image source="calculator.png">
        <shortdescription>sample of a calculator</shortdescription>
    </image>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{How to use a calculator}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        To start the calculator press the <m>{\color{green}\text{on}}</m> button.
    </p>
    <p>
         Given a number to work out its square, for example given <m>3</m>:
    </p>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Press the key that has the number <m>3</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Press the key <m>x^2</m>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Press the key <m>=</m>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Read the number on the screen of the calculator.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    <p>
        To find the square of a decimal number e.g 4.7:
    </p>
    <p>
        Press the keys <m>4</m> then <m>.</m> finally press <m>7</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
        Press the key <m>x^2</m> which means square.
    </p>
    <p>
         Press the key <m>=</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Then read the number on the screen of the calculator.
    </p>
    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
               Use a calculator to work out the squares of the following numbers: 
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
